  "prompt": "Are there legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several legal frameworks designed to combat money laundering:\n\n1. International Frameworks\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n\n2. National Legislation\n- Bank Secrecy Act (USA)\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) regulations\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) requirements\n- Suspicious Activity Reporting (SAR) mandates\n\n3. Key Regulatory Approaches\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Customer due diligence\n- Mandatory reporting of large/suspicious transactions\n- International information sharing\n- Strict penalties for non-compliance\n\n4. Financial Institution Responsibilities\n- Implementing internal control systems\n- Conducting risk assessments\n- Training staff on detection methods\n- Reporting suspicious activities\n\n5. Global Enforcement\n- Collaboration between law enforcement agencies\n- Cross-border information exchange\n- Coordinated investigations\n- Asset seizure and recovery mechanisms\n\nThese frameworks aim to prevent criminals from disguising illegally obtained funds as legitimate income and disrupt financial criminal networks.",
